	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49501><span id= >Tinkerbear</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>CHA is not important to a Necro at all. It has nothing to do with successful fear or spell hits. I am a 61 Iksar necro and my CHA is 18. Very very rarely does my fear not hit or my spells get resisted. If CHA were necessary for this to be true then I would still be level 8. Please don't steer upcoming necros the wrong way. Fellow bonecasters screw CHA, build that mana pool. However, things do cost quite a bit more at the vendor.<br><br>Razorheart Bloodreaver<br>61 Warlock of Cazic<br>E-Marr</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
